# [[dental|Dental]] [[prosthetic]] replacing a missing [[tooth]] by a bridging piece which is [[glue|glued]] to the backs of the [[adjacent]] teeth (as opposed to an ordinary dental [[bridge]] which is attached by grinding down the adjacent teeth and covering them).
#: 2005: ''Maryland bridges work best when the teeth are front teeth adjoining healthy teeth that do not have large fillings.'' &mdash; Dr. Azar-Mehr [http://www.azarmehr.com/dental-services/crowns-bridges.htm]